The paper deals with gaze tracking in the context of driving, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of Advanced Driver Assistance Systems (ADAS) also suggests a potential connection to robotics (cs.RO). The paper also involves machine learning techniques for classification, which could fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
